04/11/2004
ESSEN, Germany -- Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder said Wednesday (3 November) that he believes Bulgaria and Romania will be prepared to join the EU in 2007.
Speaking at an investment conference in Essen, Schroeder predicted Romania would complete accession talks with the EU this year.
He also urged the two countries to step up efforts to resolve remaining issues, such as corruption and judicial reform delays.
(Deutsche Welle, Nine o'clock - 03/11/04)
